39: /**
40:  * This class is used for specifying the set of expected configurations. For each configuration, you can specify
41:  * the name, the type, the default value, the documentation, the group information, the order in the group,
42:  * the width of the configuration value and the name suitable for display in the UI.
43:  *
44:  * You can provide special validation logic used for single configuration validation by overriding {@link Validator}.
45:  *
46:  * Moreover, you can specify the dependents of a configuration. The valid values and visibility of a configuration
47:  * may change according to the values of other configurations. You can override {@link Recommender} to get valid
48:  * values and set visibility of a configuration given the current configuration values.
49:  *
50:  * <p/>
51:  * To use the class:
52:  * <p/>
53:  * <pre>
